Dashboard coding standards

- Server components by default.
- Use client components only for state, browser APIs, drag/drop, forms, or interactivity.
- Type every boundary. Use existing Supabase generated types.
- Reuse existing UI primitives before creating new ones.
- Keep styling minimal, clean, editorial, fast.
- Use Tailwind patterns already present in repo.
- No new dependencies without approval.
- Prefer small reusable components over large page files.
- Keep DB logic in lib/db/*, not inside UI components.
- Keep business logic out of JSX.
- Respect current route patterns and naming conventions.
- Do not refactor unrelated files.
- If a task expands beyond requested scope, stop and ask.
- New code must not introduce lint or type errors.
